race.comment: While the majority of these struggle for form LYGON STREET LUIGI (1) looks primed to fire. Fitter for three runs back from a short break, placing the last two, and looks ideally placed to return to winning form. MORDIALLOC BEACH (9) has similar form finishing third two back then a fast finishing fourth latest. Looks hard to hold out late. SUNSET BEAUTY (10) is third-up and should be ready to find best. Winning rider back aboard and gets chance. SORRY SAILOR (5) is better than recent form suggests. Below best last time the start prior struggled on the heavy. Course and distance winner three back and off a much better draw will enjoy a soft run and launch late.
